result.name: Empire Hotel Kowloon - Tsim Sha Tsui

reviews.text:
My family was invited to a Birthday Party at the basement cafe.   The renovation of the lobby and restaurant was tacky.   It seems go back in time to the 70s.   

The soup and spaghetti she served was average.   Actually the flavor was not too d but the utensils and interior decoration were really a drag.

The service was average too.

I guess the price was quite affordable projected by the quality.   However,  the venue was just perfect for a small party like 30 guests.

Easy transfer from the airport via train and the free K4 bus transfer. The bus stops immediately across the road from the hotel. Checking in was easy and we were given the key and told which floor to find the room on our own without assistance. 

The lighting was very strange they are pushbutton switches which you have to hold momentarily until the light would either turn on or off but we had difficulty trying to turn off lights eventually in the middle of the night when we tried to use the bathroom we accidentally turned on the heat lamp which we could not turn off. We called assistance and when someone arrived they had to call the hotel engineer who came up and turn the power off to reset the lights and then return the power back on.

The beds are big and comfortable with hard and soft pillows. 

Breakfast is superb and probably one of the best I have the privilege to enjoy. 
Breakfast sessions can be very busy and there’s plenty of seating. Chefs are working tirelessly to replenish freshly cooked dishes.
The room was rather small but service was amazing and they had a phone I could take to use internet outside so I didnt have to use any extra roaming. Near the hot spots in HK.
Nice hotel and nice shopping area around.

The front desk service was standard. The room was standard. However, compared with the size it was quiet generous. Normally the hotel room in HK are quiet small. Very happy about the location and swimming pool of hotel which we enjoy a lot.
